AUDIO: 'or sixth token, it falls apart because each guess isn\'t really looking at the ones before it. DeepSeek\'s fix is to bolt a tiny lightweight head onto the fast model, so each token actually pays attention to what comes before it. And'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'they also added a scheduler that decides how far ahead to draft based on how busy the system is. Light load, you would draft more. Heavy load, pull it back so you\'re not wasting compute. So, here\'s'

